{% extends "core.twig" %}

{% block content %}

<div class="row">
    <div clasS="span5">
        <h2 style="font-weight:100"><b class="dw-logo">Datawrapper</b> is an open source tool helping everyone to create simple, correct and embeddable charts in minutes.</h2>
        <img src="/static/img/chart.png" alt="" style="margin-bottom:20px"/>


        </div>
    <div clasS="span4">
        <p>We are bridging the gap between journalists and the newest Javascript-visualization libraries such as D3.js, Raphael and others. We make it easier to "wrap" the data into these libraries without coding. Datawrapper minimizes the time needed to create a chart and thus helps data journalists everywhere in the world. </p>

        <p>The benefits in short:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Simple to use, open source, CSS access, no logo.</li>
            <li>Users can test the online version, organizations can download to their own server for data security, full control and CMS integration.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Learn more about Datawrapper on datastories.de</p>
    </div>
    <div class="span3">
        <div class="login-form form-vertical well">
            <h3>Login / Sign Up</h3>
            <input id="login-email" type="text" class="input-large" value="" placeholder="email" />
            <input id="login-pwd" type="password" class="input-large" value="" placeholder="password" /><br />
            <a id="btn-login" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Login</a>
            or <a href="#login" class="btn btn-large">Sign Up</a>
        </div>
        <p>Not convinced, yet?</p>
        <p>
        <a href="/chart/create" class="btn btn-info"><i class="icon-chevron-right icon-white"></i> Try Datawrapper now!</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

{{ parent() }}
{% endblock %}